Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I go to Page 04 of Head MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Ischemia' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled

And 'Localization' tab is enabled and preselected
And 'Ischemia area I' tab is enabled
And 'Ischemia area II' tab is enabled
And 'Vascular occlusion' tab is enabled

When I select 'Ischemia area I' tab
Then 'Lacunary' radio button is enabled
And 'Territorial' radio button is enabled
And 'Border zone' radio button is enabled
And 'Cortical' radio button is enabled

And 'Signal T2 FLAIR' slide bar is enabled

And 'No FLAIR/DWI mismatch' radio button is enabled
And 'FLAIR hyperintense area < diffusion restricted area (mismatch)' radio button is enabled
And 'FLAIR hyperintense area = diffusion restricted area' radio button is enabled

And 'T1w signal' slide bar is enabled

When I select 'Lacunary' radio button
Then 'Perifocal gliosis fringe' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ã‰tat lacunaire' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Territorial' radio button
Then 'Wedge-shaped configuration' checkbox is enabled
And 'White matter affected' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cortex affected' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Border zone' radio button
Then 'String of pearls aspect' checkbox is enabled

When I set 'Signal T2 FLAIR' slider to position Hyperintense
Then it stays on this position

When I select 'No FLAIR/DWI mismatch' radio button
Then radio button is selected

When I select 'FLAIR hyperintense area < diffusion restricted area (mismatch)' radio button
Then radio button is selected

When I select 'FLAIR hyperintense area = diffusion restricted area' radio button
Then radio button is selected

When I set 'T1w signal' slider to position Hyperintense
Then it stays on this position




